
[1]layer

   LA'YER, n. la'er. [from lay, the verb.]

   1. A stratum; a bed; a body spread over another; as a layer of clay or
   of sand.

   2. A shoot or twig of a plant, not detached from the stock, laid under
   ground for growth or propagation.

   3. A hen that lays eggs.
